Prime Nightmare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eliezeroferudin>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 824<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/03 9:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1> Regarding what appears to be the underlying issue:  Role-play is Role-play.  Some people define 'Evil' as simply RPing what they consider 'evil.'  Other people define evil as being nothing more than your Race/Class/Deity combo.<br>
<br>
But those are OOC distinctions.  As soon as you try and take that philosophical difference between Players into IC, you are doomed to have a bad ending.<br>
<br>
&gt;<br>
<br>
No.  Solusek Ro would (imho) most accurately be described as a Neutral deity.  But he is neutral in the sense that he is pretty much self-centered and has absolutely no interest in the 'struggles' of the gods or races of Norrath.  He is interested purely in Power.  Not the APPLICATION of Power, whuch seems to be where the conflict between Good and Evil largely comes from.<br>
<br>
From an EQ/FV standpoint, I'd say he was a Discordant deity.  The only prohibition on his followers in the FV Alignment system (on top of Racial restrictions of course) was that his followers could not be Ordered.<br>
<br>
So, as an Erudite Wizard of Solusek Ro, my Alignment choices were Neutral Good or Neutral Evil.<br>
<br>
There CAN be Evil Erudites who do NOT worship Cazic Thule, but they are not Evil through Religion but rather through choice.<br>
<br>
As we no longer HAVE Alignments, exactly what constitutes Good and Evil is largely a matter of personal opinion - there are no right and wrong answers.<br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that Race is a big factor.  In my OPINION, not saying anyone has to agree with me, I think some Races are presdestined - Tier'dal/Ogres/Trolls/Iksar for Evil, and Wood Elves/High Elves for Good.<br>
<br>
All other Races, in my view, have the capacity to choose.<br>
<br>
Humans, Erudites, and Gnomes all have the ability to be Class/Deity combos that 'mark one as Good or Evil (Necros/SKs/Paladins)<br>
<br>
Barbarians, Halflings, Vah Shir don't have anything that is 'obviously' Evil, but I don't think it is that much of a stretch to assume that those who can be neutral and agnotic and such can't slide into evil.<br>
<br>
So then it becomes 'What is evil enough?'  -- And that is an OOC question for some and an IC one for others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daramor>daramor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Lord of All That Is Unholy</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/03 9:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1> Just copying your explanation, you made things clearer in my mind and i think you. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://dcaussinus.free.fr/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rikkonfv>RikkonFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/03 11:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drama</span><hr size=1> sorry to see you go Inthul <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
